/**
 * @file plotting.pxd
 * @brief Cython declaration file for the @c plotting C++ class and the
 *        Python wrappers @c BasePlotting, @c TH1F, @c TH2F, and @c TLine.
 * @details Wraps the @c plotting class (inheriting @c notification and
 *          @c tools) which manages per-histogram styling and data arrays, and
 *          provides Python-level histogram classes.
 */

/**
 * @class BasePlotting
 * @brief Python base wrapper for @c plotting.
 * @details Owns a `plotting*` and the Matplotlib figure/axes objects.
 *          All plotting classes inherit from this and share the styling
 *          properties listed below.  Call `SaveFigure()` to produce the
 *          output file.
 *
 * **Serialisation methods:**
 * - `dump(path: str = "", name: str = "")` ‚Äî Pickle to
 *   `<OutputDirectory>/<Filename>.pkl`.
 * - `load(path: str = "", name: str = "") -> BasePlotting | None` ‚Äî Unpickle
 *   a previously saved instance.
 *
 * **Rendering method:**
 * - `SaveFigure()` ‚Äî Apply all style settings, compile the plot via
 *   `__compile__`, and write the figure to disk (PNG or PGF when LaTeX is
 *   enabled).
 *
 * **Style properties (read/write):**
 * - `Hatch` (str) ‚Äî Matplotlib hatch pattern string (e.g. `"/"`, `"x"`).
 * - `DPI` (int) ‚Äî Dots per inch for the saved figure; set to 800
 *   automatically in ATLAS style.
 * - `Style` (str) ‚Äî Plot style name; `"ATLAS"` activates the mplhep ATLAS
 *   style sheet.
 * - `CapSize` (float) ‚Äî Cap size for error-bar ends.
 * - `ErrorBars` (bool) ‚Äî If True draw symmetric error bars on histograms.
 * - `Filename` (str) ‚Äî Base filename (without extension) of the output file.
 * - `OutputDirectory` (str) ‚Äî Directory in which the figure is saved.
 * - `FontSize` (float) ‚Äî Base font size for all text elements.
 * - `AxisSize` (float) ‚Äî Font size used for axis tick labels.
 * - `LegendSize` (float) ‚Äî Font size used for the legend.
 * - `TitleSize` (float) ‚Äî Font size used for the figure title.
 * - `UseLateX` (bool) ‚Äî Render text through LuaLaTeX; also saves a `.pgf`
 *   alongside the PNG.
 * - `xScaling` (float) ‚Äî Figure width scaling factor (inches).
 * - `yScaling` (float) ‚Äî Figure height scaling factor (inches).
 * - `AutoScaling` (bool) ‚Äî Let Matplotlib autoscale the axes.
 * - `LineStyle` (str) ‚Äî Matplotlib linestyle string (e.g. `"-"`, `"--"`).
 * - `Title` (str) ‚Äî Figure title; if `ShowCount` is True and data exist the
 *   total count is appended automatically.
 * - `xTitle` (str) ‚Äî x-axis label.
 * - `yTitle` (str) ‚Äî y-axis label.  The placeholder `<units>` is replaced
 *   with the computed bin width during rendering.
 * - `xLogarithmic` (bool) ‚Äî Use a log scale on the x-axis.
 * - `yLogarithmic` (bool) ‚Äî Use a log scale on the y-axis.
 * - `xStep` (float) ‚Äî Fixed tick spacing on the x-axis; 0 disables.
 * - `yStep` (float) ‚Äî Fixed tick spacing on the y-axis; 0 disables.
 * - `xMin` (float) ‚Äî Lower bound of the x-axis range.
 * - `yMin` (float) ‚Äî Lower bound of the y-axis range.
 * - `xMax` (float) ‚Äî Upper bound of the x-axis range.
 * - `yMax` (float) ‚Äî Upper bound of the y-axis range.
 * - `Overflow` (str | int) ‚Äî Overflow handling strategy: `"none"`, `"sum"`,
 *   or an integer (0 ‚Üí `"none"`, non-zero ‚Üí `"sum"`).
 * - `Color` (str) ‚Äî Hex colour string for this histogram; a random colour is
 *   generated on first read if none has been set.
 * - `Colors` (list[str]) ‚Äî List of colours when drawing multiple series.
 */

/**
 * @class TH1F
 * @brief 1D histogram Python wrapper (inherits @c BasePlotting).
 * @details Manages a primary data array and an optional list of overlay
 *          histograms with stacking, scaling, and comparison support.
 *
 * **Data properties (read/write):**
 * - `xData` (list[float]) ‚Äî Raw data values to be histogrammed.
 * - `xBins` (int | list[float]) ‚Äî Number of uniform bins (int) or explicit
 *   bin-edge list (variable binning).
 * - `Weights` (list[float]) ‚Äî Per-event weights aligned with `xData`.
 * - `CrossSection` (float) ‚Äî Process cross-section in pb; used with
 *   `IntegratedLuminosity` to scale yields.
 * - `IntegratedLuminosity` (float) ‚Äî Integrated luminosity in fb‚Åª¬π.
 * - `HistFill` (str) ‚Äî Histogram fill style passed to `hep.histplot`
 *   (e.g. `"fill"`, `"step"`, `"errorbar"`).
 * - `Stacked` (bool) ‚Äî If True overlay histograms are drawn stacked.
 * - `LineWidth` (float) ‚Äî Line width for histogram outlines.
 * - `Alpha` (float) ‚Äî Opacity of the histogram fill (0.0‚Äì1.0).
 * - `Density` (bool) ‚Äî If True normalise to unit area before plotting.
 * - `Marker` (str) ‚Äî Matplotlib marker style for errorbar plots.
 * - `xLabels` (dict[str, float]) ‚Äî Categorical x-axis labels mapped to bin
 *   weights (enables string-category histograms).
 * - `ShowCount` (bool) ‚Äî Append the total event count to the histogram title.
 *
 * **Read-only property:**
 * - `counts` (numpy.ndarray | list) ‚Äî Bin counts of the compiled histogram.
 *
 * **Methods:**
 * - `FX(val=None)` ‚Äî Set the comparison function used when a reference
 *   histogram is present: `"ratio"` (default), `"chi2"`, or a custom
 *   callable `f(H1, H2, ax, ...)`.
 * - `KStest(hist: TH1F) -> tuple` ‚Äî Perform a two-sample Kolmogorov‚ÄìSmirnov
 *   test between this histogram's data and `hist`'s data within the current
 *   axis range; returns `(statistic, p-value)`.
 */

/**
 * @class TH2F
 * @brief 2D histogram Python wrapper (inherits @c BasePlotting).
 * @details Renders a 2D colour-map histogram using `hep.hist2dplot`.
 *
 * **Data properties (read/write):**
 * - `xBins` (int | list[float]) ‚Äî x-axis binning (uniform int or variable
 *   edge list).
 * - `yBins` (int | list[float]) ‚Äî y-axis binning (uniform int or variable
 *   edge list).
 * - `xLabels` (dict[str, float]) ‚Äî Categorical x-axis labels.
 * - `yLabels` (dict[str, float]) ‚Äî Categorical y-axis labels.
 * - `xData` (list[float]) ‚Äî x-coordinate values.
 * - `yData` (list[float]) ‚Äî y-coordinate values.
 * - `Weights` (list[float]) ‚Äî Per-entry weights.
 */

/**
 * @class TLine
 * @brief Line-graph Python wrapper (inherits @c BasePlotting).
 * @details Supports error shading and multiple overlaid lines.  Typically
 *          used for ROC curves, efficiency curves, and training histories.
 *
 * **Data properties (read/write):**
 * - `xData` (list[float]) ‚Äî x-coordinate values for the primary line.
 * - `yData` (list[float]) ‚Äî y-coordinate values for the primary line.
 * - `Marker` (str) ‚Äî Matplotlib marker style.
 * - `yDataUp` (list[float]) ‚Äî Upper error-band boundary aligned with
 *   `xData`.
 * - `yDataDown` (list[float]) ‚Äî Lower error-band boundary aligned with
 *   `xData`.
 * - `LineWidth` (float) ‚Äî Width of the drawn line.
 * - `Alpha` (float) ‚Äî Opacity of the line (0.0‚Äì1.0).
 */

